-- Summers: ‘Almost’ Every Indicator Favorable
-- B y   C h e y e n n e   H o p k i n s
-- 2012-02-05T14:34:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/summers-almost-every-indicator-favorable.html
Larry Summers , a former economic
adviser to the Obama administration, said “almost every
indicator on the economy is favorable” while Glen Hubbard, an
adviser to the Romney campaign and the former chairman of the
 Council of Economic Advisers  under President  George W. Bush ,
said Obama is “standing in the way” of a recovery.  Both former officials appeared today on ABC’s “This
Week.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cheyenne Hopkins in Washington at 
 chopkins19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
